## Appendix A — doctor report template (T12)

> Provenance
> - Authoritative paradigm: Böckeler "evaluate harness coverage and quality" — distinct from `/hx-analyze` (planning artifacts) and `/hx-review` (impl vs plan); this one checks the harness mechanism's self-consistency, drift, and eval regression
> - Investigation protocol: scan rule ↔ guardrail mapping (constitution principle ↔ playbook step / lint / arch-test / review check); validate every `path:line` and symbol citation across knowledge + active specs; diff `.harness/knowledge/architecture.md` anchors vs the live module graph; sample recent `specs/*/design.md` for §12.4 A scoring; replay `.harness/evals/` samples and compare to baseline (first-try-pass · clarify-questions · review must-fix · rework)
> - Output form: tri-tier self-check report — **CRITICAL** (broken refs · budget exceeded · eval regression) · **WARNING** (drift · dead rules · contradictions) · **INFO** (prune candidates · design-score deltas) — with concrete remediation per finding

```markdown
